answers.answer: If you think something is wrong always call your Dr. That's what they are there for.
I would call the Dr because it could be your blood pressure or something else. Has your vision been blurry?
my vision hasnt been blurry. I'm just kinda worried that something is wrong. I am most likely gonna call the doctor soon. just wantedsome opinions on it first.

When I was 36 weeks, I had higher than normal bp and I was told I needed to be induced just as a precaution. I suppose Dr knows best but if your worried, call them with your symptoms. Its nothing to mess around with

question: so I'm 37+5 preggo & on tues I had a dr appt my blood pressure was higher than normal but not to worry about. I had no protein in my urine either however I have had trouble breathing / sometimes a weird pain in my chest / upper belly. my right foot & hand is much more swollen than my left & I have been getting headaches on & off that dont go away with tylenol. I have also gained 6 lbs this week. I feel like I'm having signs of preeclampsia but my blood pressure was fine & no protein in urine. should I call the doctor?? or go to ER?
title: advice??
